<h3>...Where Everything We Do is Always A Cut Above the Rest!</h3>
&nbsp;
When you take your pet to a "typical" grooming shop, you have to make sure the staff is friendly and the groomers are gentle. If you love and care for your pet (as most people do), you'll probably even find yourself worrying about whether your furry friend will feel safe there during such an intimate experience such as being bathed. And speaking of being bathed, does the shop take care to keep their tools and workspaces clean to prevent the spread of fungus, disease, etc? Do they let students groom the pets? The truth is, you really have a lot to consider before leaving your pet in the hands of the average pet grooming shop.
<h4>Good thing A Cut Above Pet Salons aren't average.</h4>
When you walk into one of our salons, you'll immediately notice the difference: We're not just a grooming shop -- we're a <em>pet salon</em>. We take care of your furry friends the same way we treat our own: we give each pet a genuine, gentle spa treatment during their stay with us.
&nbsp;
All of our services, from our basic teeth cleaning to our full spa package, are performed by certified professionals who have passed through our rigorous <a href="pet-grooming-apprenticeship-program/" title="A Cut Above Pet Grooming Apprenticeship Program" target="_blank">apprenticeship program</a>. Because this is their chosen career (not just a part-time job), you can rest assured that the people caring for your pet know what they're doing -- and they really care about the details.
